[size=5][center][b]House Rules[/b][/center][/size]

An F4SE plugin that exposes high-impact vanilla Fallout 4 settings through a single MCM menu. The goal: give you the tools to tune vanilla mechanics so they fit a modded playthrough. Everything is a runtime tweak to settings the engine already has. No ESP, no plugin-slot cost.

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/fallout4/mods/42147]F4SE[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/fallout4/mods/47327]Address Library for F4SE[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/fallout4/mods/56235]Mod Configuration Menu (MCM)[/url]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]

All three main Fallout 4 runtimes:
[list]
[*]OG 1.10.163 (pre-NG)
[*]NG 1.10.984
[*]AE 1.11.x (1.11.191 tested)
[/list]

[size=4][b]What it does[/b][/size]

MCM pages cover:
[list]
[*][b]Survival Unlocks[/b] - opt-in toggles for console, manual / auto saves, fast travel, compass enemies / locations, chem / ammo weight, carry weight, god mode, re-entering Survival
[*][b]Survival[/b] - kill-switches for Hunger/Thirst, Sleep, Diseases, Adrenaline + ~38 tuning sliders for the manager script
[*][b]Magnitudes[/b] - stimpak / RadAway / Rad-X / food healing and hunger / thirst / sleep penalty severity
[*][b]Difficulty[/b] - per-tier incoming / outgoing damage, XP, legendary chance / rarity, effect duration / magnitude
[*][b]Character[/b] - AP pool, sprint cost, carry capacity, max-health scaling, AP / health regen
[*][b]Damage Formulas, Power Armor, VATS[/b] - raw damage factors, jetpack / fusion core / PA durability, VATS engage and player damage
[*][b]Economy, Progression, Skills, Sneak[/b] - barter prices, crafting / lockpick / mine XP, pickpocket / hacking / lockpicking, sneak attack and detection
[*][b]Combat Perks, Settlements, Companions Affinity[/b] - perk-trigger chances, workshop / settler caps, per-reaction affinity deltas
[/list]

Full per-slider reference (defaults, units, behavior notes): [url=https://github.com/northaxosky/HouseRules/blob/master/docs/FEATURES.md]docs/FEATURES.md[/url]

[size=4][b]Caveats[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]The carry-weight unlock and the Survival kill-switches need a save reload after toggling for immediate effect. Otherwise they apply on the manager script's next tick (a few in-game minutes).
[*]Sliders apply when you close the pause menu. Magnitude changes wait for the next consumable use, the Pip-Boy tooltip caches the old value until then.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Source & bug reports[/b][/size]

[list]
